metadata.name: Nietzsche was right
metadata.description:
It was Monday 2016.
I had a hangover, then a cigarette on an empty stomach and a cup of strong coffee.
You stood there with your bare torso drenched in sunlight. Music was playing that we forgot to turn off the night before. 

My father called me and told me I was the worst daughter on earth.
Nietzsche was right. There is no God, which means you don't exist.
